ls0 ws0">reflected in the names by which prophets were </div><div class="t m409 x80 h69 y849 ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">known in OT times: seer </div><div class="t ma22 x62 h20 y439 ff9 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(chozeh </div><div class="t m2bf xc8 h69 y439 ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">or </div><div class="t m634 xc7 h20 y439 ff9 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ro&apos;eh ) </div><div class="t m80a x18f h69 y1bc ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and </div><div class="t m466 x80 h69 y9ab ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">prophet </div><div class="t mdc8 x1c h20 y9ab ff9 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(nabi&apos;). </div><div class="t m39e x23 h69 y24c ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The title of seer was more </div><div class="t m45d x80 h69 y134c ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">common in the earlier period of Hebrew his-</div><div class="t mafc x80 h69 y450 ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tory (1 Sa 9:9). The •term used more frequently </div><div class="t m32e x80 h69 y17f ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in the OT was </div><div class="t mb57 x46 h20 y15a ff9 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nabi&apos;, </div><div class="t m9a1 x8c h69 y15a ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&apos;prophet,&apos; which desig-</div><div class="t m316 x80 h69 y350 ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nated him as God&apos;s spokesman. As a &apos;seer&apos; the </div><div class="t ma9a x80 h69 y606 ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">prophet discerned God&apos;s will, and as &apos;prophet&apos; </div><div class="t mf57 x98 h69 y10b ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">he conveyed it to others.&quot;—SDA </div><div class="t mfc xc7 h20 y10b ff9 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bible Dic-</div><div class="t m4c3 x80 h20 y28e ff9 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tionary, </div><div class="t m673 x20 h69 y28e ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">page 879. </div><div class="t m2a3 x80 h49 y70 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON OUTLINE </div><div class="t m12c x80 h49 y6c2 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t mc7 x1e h49 y6c2 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Call, Isa. 6:8, 9 </div><div class="t m814 x80 h49 y186 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><di